1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on response generation in human-to-human dialogues. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category as the paper proposes a data-driven approach to response generation using neural models. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper discusses the optimization goal of the model and proposes a regularization term to improve the model's performance. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper deals with neural models and their limitations in generating diverse responses. 
5. cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely category as the paper does not deal with sound or audio data, but it is still a possibility as the paper may discuss the use of sound in human-to-human dialogues.
